message.content:
An electric guitar is a type of guitar that uses pickups and electronic amplification to produce sound. 
It typically has a solid body and a thinner neck than an acoustic guitar. 
Electric guitars come in a variety of colors, including black, white, red, sunburst, and metallic shades. 
The body of an electric guitar may be made of wood, metal, or a combination of materials. 
It usually has six strings, although seven- and eight-string models are also available. 
Electric guitars are commonly used in rock, metal, and blues music, among other genres. 
They can be found in music stores, recording studios, and on stage during live concerts.
